OL,3,CUp to #25 billion in tax rises may be
OL,4,Cneeded for 'no return to austerity'
OL,5,Cpledge
OL,7,F"There will be no return to austerity".
OL,9,FIt was one of Labour's keys manifesto
OL,10,Fpledges, designed to secure power.
OL,12,FIt's still not at all clear what the
OL,13,Fparty meant by this commitment but,
OL,14,Fbroadly speaking, it was a signal that
OL,15,FLabour could be relied on to protect
OL,16,Fspending on public services if it won
OL,17,Fthe election.
