OL,3,CUp to #25 billion in tax rises may be
OL,4,Cneeded for 'no return to austerity'
OL,5,Cpledge
OL,7,FThis is the money the government uses
OL,8,Fto fund the running costs of public
OL,9,Fservices and the delivery of welfare
OL,10,Fand benefits. This includes paying the
OL,11,Fsalaries of public workers (nurses,
OL,12,Fteachers and police); the running
OL,13,Fcosts of schools, hospitals and
OL,14,Fgovernment departments; the payments
OL,15,Fof universal credit and the state
OL,16,Fpension; and interest payments on the
OL,17,Fnation's debts.
