OL,5,Cpledge
OL,7,FSecondly, there is "capital spending".
OL,8,FThis is the money the government
OL,9,Finvests, building stuff like roads,
OL,10,Frailways, schools and hospitals.
OL,12,FIf Reeves changes her debt rule - that
OL,13,F"debt must be falling as a share of
OL,14,Fnational income by the fifth year of
OL,15,Fthe forecast" - she would have more
OL,16,Fscope to borrow for capital spending.
OL,18,FBut Labour's manifesto also contains a
OL,19,Fpledge that the "day-to-day costs" of
OL,20,Fproviding public services "are met by
OL,21,Frevenues".
