OL,3,CUp to #25 billion in tax rises may be
OL,4,Cneeded for 'no return to austerity'
OL,5,Cpledge
OL,7,FAnalysis by the IFS, based on economic
OL,8,Fforecasts prepared by Citi, suggest
OL,9,FRachel Reeves would need to raise
OL,10,Ftaxes by around #16 billion a year if
OL,11,Fshe wishes to balance the current
OL,12,Fbudget by 2028/29 and ensure that the
OL,13,Fbudgets of all government departments
OL,14,Frise in line with national income.
OL,16,FThis is in addition to the #9 billion
OL,17,Fof tax rises set out in Labour's
OL,18,Fmanifesto - the largest of which comes
OL,19,Ffrom a clampdown on tax avoidance and
OL,20,F"further closing non-dom loopholes".
