OL,4,Cneeded for 'no return to austerity'
OL,5,Cpledge
OL,7,FThat's a total of #25 billion.
OL,9,FLabour's pledges not to raise income
OL,10,Ftax and corporation tax or to increase
OL,11,FNational Insurance or VAT, as well as
OL,12,Fits promise not to increase taxes "for
OL,13,Fworking people" make it hard for
OL,14,FRachel Reeves to implement a single,
OL,15,Fsimple, large tax increase.
OL,17,FIn the Commons yesterday, Sir Kier
OL,18,FStarmer did not rule out that he was
OL,19,Fconsidering increasing the rate of
OL,20,Fnational insurance contributions paid
OL,21,Fby employers.
