OL,5,Cpledge
OL,7,FThe IFS concedes the chancellor find
OL,8,Fherself in an "unenviable" position.
OL,10,FTaxes are already at an historically
OL,11,Fhigh level, and national debt is high
OL,12,Fand rising and the interest the
OL,13,Fgovernment pays on that debt has risen
OL,14,Fsharply. Meanwhile, public services
OL,15,Fare visibly struggling.
OL,17,FCarl Emerson, director of IFS, says
OL,18,Fthe UK used to be a "low-spender" when
OL,19,Fit came to the provision of public
OL,20,Fservices but that's no longer the case.
