OL,7,F"We have developed an appetite to
OL,8,Fspend like the average economy," he
OL,9,Fsays, "but we haven't matched that
OL,10,Fwith a desire to tax like the average
OL,11,Feconomy".
OL,13,FIn his view, the option is pretty
OL,14,Fclear. Either we decide want a bigger
OL,15,Fstate and we pay for it or we decide
OL,16,Fthat the state should so less.
OL,18,FA stark choice and not one we saw in
OL,19,FLabour's manifesto.
